Alapis Plans 98.1 Million Euro Capital Increase, Euro2day Says

-- B y   N a t a l i e   W e e k s
-- 
2011-03-09T08:23:12Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-09/alapis-plans-98-1-million-euro-capital-increase-euro2day-says.html
Alapis Holdings SA plans a 98.1
million euro ($136.3 million) share capital increase and the
issue of two convertible bonds of as much as 300 million euros,
 euro2day.gr  reported.  The funds will be used to boost investment in the generic
drug sector and to refinance and repay company debt, the Athens-
based news site said, without saying where it got the
information.  Alapis will offer 2 new shares for each one held at one
euro a piece, following a reverse split of its stock, euro2day
said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Natalie Weeks in Athens 
 nweeks2@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Angela Cullen at 
 acullen8@bloomberg.net  